Package: logitech-trueforce-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, dkms
# The pre-split logitech-trueforce-dkms shipped the userspace tools too;
# recommending logi-dd keeps upgrades (and "install the driver, get the
# ecosystem") whole while still allowing a lean module-only install.
Recommends: logi-dd
Suggests: oversteer
Description: DKMS kernel driver for Logitech TrueForce direct-drive wheels
 Force feedback, TrueForce texture routing, and G HUB-equivalent settings
 exposed through sysfs for the Logitech RS50 and G PRO direct-drive racing
 wheels. The module is built and installed for the running kernel by DKMS,
 and rebuilt automatically on kernel upgrades.
 .
 The module is named hid-logitech-dd and is scoped to the direct-drive
 wheel USB IDs (c276 RS50 native, c272 G PRO Xbox/PC and RS50 compat, c268
 G PRO PS/PC). It coexists with the in-tree hid-logitech-hidpp driver,
 which continues to serve every other Logitech device, so no blacklist is
 needed.
 .
 Ships both udev rules: wheel sysfs/hidraw access for the "input" group,
 and /dev/uhid access for the logi-ffb proxy from the logi-dd package.

Package: logi-dd
Section: utils
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, logitech-trueforce-dkms
# python3: the shim installer edits the wine prefix registry with it.
Recommends: python3
Suggests: wine
Description: Terminal tools for Logitech TrueForce direct-drive wheels
 The complete headless toolset for the logitech-trueforce driver: logi-dd,
 a terminal settings UI, logi-ffb, a DirectInput force-feedback proxy,
 logi-tf-sim, a simulated-TrueForce daemon driven by game telemetry, and
 logitech-trueforce-install-shim, the TrueForce SDK shim installer for
 Proton prefixes.
 .
 TrueForce in Proton sims additionally needs Logitech's proprietary signed
 SDK DLLs, which are not shipped by this package; see the driver package's
 Getting Started guide.

Package: logi-dd-gui
Section: utils
Architecture: any
# The Slint GUI dlopen's its windowing/input/GL stack at runtime rather
# than linking it, so ${shlibs:Depends} alone would miss those libraries
# (derived from `ldd`/`strings` on the built binary). fontconfig/freetype
# are linked and covered by ${shlibs:Depends}, but stay listed for clarity.
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, logi-dd,
 libwayland-client0, libwayland-egl1, libxkbcommon0,
 libxkbcommon-x11-0, libx11-6, libx11-xcb1, libxcb1, libxcursor1, libxi6,
 libxrender1, libegl1, libgl1, libfontconfig1, libfreetype6
Description: Graphical settings app for Logitech TrueForce wheels
 logi-dd-gui, a graphical settings app (GPL-3.0-or-later; see
 debian/copyright) for the logitech-trueforce driver, with a desktop menu
 entry. Covers wheel settings, LIGHTSYNC, response curves, the game-helper
 setup pages, and a test section.
